$ SAS: proc format
@ proc format

`proc format` can be used to create a customized → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/formats-informats[format] besides the ones provided by SAS.

{ Creating a range format

  gh|about-SAS|/programming/proc/format/value.range.sas||

}
{ Formatting a date time #proc-format-date-time

  The following picture allows to display a → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/date#sas-date-time[date time] as `dd.mm.yyyy hh24:mi:ss`:
  gh|about-SAS|/programming/proc/format/picture/ddmmyyyy_hh24miss.sas||

  It looks as though the formats are somehow modelled after → development/misc/strftime.

  See also the → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/formats-informats/datetime[datetime.] format.

}

